
Overview of noun loophole

The noun loophole has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (2) loophole -- (an ambiguity (especially one in the text of a law or contract) that makes it possible to evade a difficulty or obligation)
2. (1) loophole -- (a small hole in a fortified wall; for observation or discharging weapons)
